title: Print, "Chef dec Indiens (Indian Chief), plate 8 from Caravanne du Sultan a la Mecque (Caravan of a Sultan Going to Mecca)", 1748
inscribed: Inscribed across lower margin: Chef dec Indiens; J.V. del. Sc.
creditline: Museum purchase through gift of Eleanor G. Hewitt
description: Dark-skinned man with mustache leans against low wall. Both hands at belt, from which hangs long curved sword. He faces frontally, and wears stiff striped turban with fur, feathers, and pearls.
